<br>
In my opinion the BL class was made for the casual gamer because they are so easily soloable throughout their lifespan. The problem is that because the class is so new people tend to try and compare them to the other pet classes, most notably mages. The problem with that is that we are nothing like mages. Our spells for the most part suck and instead we have to melee alongside the pet in order to have the same DPS that a mage is capable of. Is this a bad thing? not in my opinion, instead it is just a different kind of play style.<br>
<br>
Now for the high end game, be ready tobe disappointed. The reality is that we as a class do not bring a great deal to the raid. At 59 we get a nice little buff that adds more hp/mana regen and stacks with most other buffs, but it really isn't a raid breaking spell. At 60 we get Savagery an extremely nice spell that will allow rogues to up their DPS very noticeably, but due to some limitations with that spell it really dosen't make much difference to the raid. So all in all we are class that most raids can live without and the reality is that shortsighted egotistic raid leaders will have no use for you. The saving grace is that Verant has stated more than once that the class is as of yet unfinished. Most of us take that to mean that we should see some tweaking that will make us more desired, one can only hope.<br>
<br>
As for gear, you are correct. There is a very limited amount of gear we can use and on top of this we share most of it with monks. This brings up the problem that even I have run into and that is the monks tend to get first shot at it. It sucks but at least in my old guild I tended to get what others didn't want or need because my guild leader thought it was more important for the clerics and shaman to get those really nice 2HB items because of their leet melee skills (note the sarcasim).<br>
<br>
Bottom line is that if you just play to have fun and/or you have a limited playtime then this class was made for you. If you are one of those people that has to play a class that every raid requires then maybe you should play a cleric. <p><BR>
